<TITLE> SC halts advance bail for 14 sugar traders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 16 (bdnews24.com)--The Supreme Court on Monday halted the bail 14 sugar traders of Jessore had secured in advance from the High Court in two separate cases accusing them of illegal hoarding. Justice Mohammed Mozammel Hossain gave the stay order, effective for four weeks, following a government petition. The judge asked the government to file leave to appeal by that time. Additional attorney general Zahirul Huq represented the state while AFM Mesbahuddin argued for the traders. The traders are Hafizur Rahman, Safiar Rahman, Rafiqul Islam, Modhusudan Saha, Alok Kumar Kundu, Sirajul Islam, Sarwar Hossain, Abdul Wahab, Anisur Rahman aka Boro Anis, Anisur Rahman aka Chhoto Anis, Abdul Odud, Raju Ahmed, Mohammed Momin and Chittaranjan Kundu. The High Court granted the 14 traders bail on Oct 6 but the Appellate Division chamber judge halted the order the next day. Agriculture marketing officer in Jessore Sujaet Hossain Khan filed the cases on Oct 1 under the Special Powers Act for hoarding sugar worth Tk 16 crore. One case was filed for illegally hoarding 3,910 sacks of sugar and another for 67,100 sacks. On Sept 26, RAB, police and National Security Intelligence officials in a raid on four stock houses of Joint Trading Corporation and Sheikh Brothers seized sugar worth Tk 16 crore. bd
